# Keep the Docker build context tiny and stable.
#
# Without this file, `COPY . .` in Dockerfile.alloy / Dockerfile.test ships the
# entire working tree — dominated by target/ (multiple GB) — on every build.
# That makes the context transfer huge AND changes the COPY layer's hash on
# every local `cargo build` (target/ churns constantly), invalidating the
# cached `RUN cargo build` layer each time. The in-image build uses a BuildKit
# cache mount at /app/target, so the host's target/ is never needed inside.

# Rust build artifacts — the big one.
target/

# Version control / project metadata.
.git/
.gitignore
.github/

# Docker files themselves (not needed inside the context).
Dockerfile.base
Dockerfile.alloy
Dockerfile.test
.dockerignore

# insta snapshot work-in-progress files.
**/*.pending-snap
**/*.snap.new

# Editor / OS cruft.
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
.DS_Store
